docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Jan. 29. -- Marked increases in the volume of United States commodities exported to Europe and Asia during December were also shown in Commerce Department figures made public today covering foreign trade for the month. Europe, however,...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Jan. 29. -- Marked increases in the volume of United States commodities exported to Europe and Asia during December were also shown in Commerce Department figures made public today covering foreign trade for the month. Europe, however, increased its importation from this country by 30 per cent. as compared with the same month of 1922.

docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges were irregular yesterday, the forward movement of Monday being succeeded by a quiet reaction which canceled the best part of the improvement which came with the settlement of the British railway strike. The market was only moderately active, however, the volume falling off with the decline.

docs.snippet: Additional evidence of improvement in the political and industrial affairs of Europe was demonstrated rather forcibly yesterday when all exchanges moved up in a series of robust gains. It was London demand again which, as on Wednesday, sent rates...
docs.lead_paragraph: Additional evidence of improvement in the political and industrial affairs of Europe was demonstrated rather forcibly yesterday when all exchanges moved up in a series of robust gains. It was London demand again which, as on Wednesday, sent rates higher, and bankers and dealers declared that the steady stream of buying orders from that centre indicated success in averting a lay-off of the dockworkers.
